Citation.sTitle: Densities and Viscosities for Binary and Ternary Mixtures of Ethanol, 2-Butanone, and 2,2,4-Trimethylpentane at T = (298.15, 308.15, and 318.15) K
Citation.sAbstract: Densities and viscosities of the ternary mixtures ethanol + 2-butanone + 2,2,4-trimethylpentane and the binary mixtures ethanol + 2-butanone, ethanol + 2,2,4-trimethylpentane, and 2-butanone + 2,2,4-trimethylpentane were measured at T = (298.15, 308.15, and 318.15) K and atmospheric pressure over the whole composition range. Densities were determined using a vibrating-tube densimeter. Viscosities were measured with an automatic Ubbelohde capillary viscometer. Excess molar volumes VE and deviations in viscosity Dh for the mixtures were derived from experimental data. The binary data were correlated with liquid composition by using the Redlich-Kister equation. For the ternary data, several polynomial equations have been tested to minimize the set of parameters for adequate correlation.
Citation.sKeyword: mixture binary ternary density viscosity ethanol 2-butanone 2,2,4-trimethylpentane
